1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,800
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:04,860
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,860 --> 00:00:09,360
My name is Catherine and today we have a very painful lesson for you.
我是Catherine，今天我们为大家准备了一堂非常痛苦的课。

4
00:00:09,360 --> 00:00:10,360
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:12,640
Today we're going to go to one of the worst places for me.
今天我们要去一个对我来说最糟糕的地方之一。

6
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:14,200
We're going to go to the dentist.
我们要去看牙医。

7
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:21,600
Okay, so the person in this dialogue has a pain in their mouth, in the tooth area.
好的，这段对话中的人嘴巴疼，牙疼。

8
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:25,240
So let's take a listen to this dialogue and when we come back, we'll be talking a little
所以让我们先听一下这段对话，等我们回来后再详细讨论。

9
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:28,240
bit more about it.
再聊一聊。

10
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:35,080
What seems to be the problem?
有什么问题吗？

11
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:37,760
I have a really bad toothache.
我牙疼得厉害。

12
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:41,480
My cheek is swollen and I can't eat anything.
我的脸颊肿了，什么都吃不了。

13
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:42,480
Let's have a look.
让我看看。

14
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:46,320
This doesn't look too good.
情况看起来不太好。

15
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:49,440
I think we may have to pull out your wisdom tooth.
我想我们可能需要拔掉你的智齿。

16
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:52,880
It's pressing against your molars and that's one of the reasons you're experiencing so
它正压着你的臼齿，这也是你感到这么疼的原因之一。

17
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:54,320
much pain.
疼得这么厉害。

18
00:00:54,320 --> 00:01:00,600
When you pull my tooth, will you also have to extract the nerve and the root?
拔牙的时候，你也要把神经和牙根抽出来吗？

19
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,040
First we will take some x-rays and see what we're dealing with.
首先我们会拍几张X光片，看看情况如何。

20
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:07,640
I also noticed a small cavity up front here, so you are going to need a filling.
我还注意到前面这里有个小蛀牙，所以你需要补牙。

21
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:12,560
I guess that's what I get for not flossing or brushing my teeth three times a day.
我想这就是我不每天用牙线或刷三次牙的后果。

22
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:16,120
It could be that or maybe you are eating too many sweets.
可能是这个原因，或者你吃太多甜食了。

23
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:25,680
In any case, I'll administer an anesthetic and you won't feel a thing.
不管怎样，我会给你打麻药，你什么感觉都不会有。

24
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:29,680
Alright we're back and obviously we're going to take a look at a lot of vocab related to
好了，我们回来了，显然我们要看看很多和看牙医以及经历一点疼痛相关的词汇。

25
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:33,160
going to the dentist and experiencing a little bit of pain.
经历一点疼痛。

26
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:40,440
So let's take a look at that in Language Takeaway.
那么让我们在“语言要点”中看看这些。

27
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:44,140
First up in Language Takeaway today we have the root of the problem.
今天“语言要点”的第一项是问题的根源。

28
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:45,520
It's a toothache.
是牙痛。

29
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:49,000
That's right, we have a really bad toothache.
没错，我们牙疼得厉害。

30
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,880
Okay well ache means pain or soreness and tooth is your tooth.
好的，“ache”意思是疼痛或酸痛，“tooth”就是你的牙齿。

31
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:57,340
So I could say, oh gosh I have a really bad toothache.
所以我可以这么说，哦天哪，我牙疼得厉害。

32
00:01:57,340 --> 00:02:01,040
That's right, that means your tooth or your teeth hurt.
没错，那意味着你的牙齿疼。

33
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:05,360
And basically you can combine it like a stomachache or headache.
基本上你可以像“stomachache”或“headache”那样组合。

34
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:06,360
Backache.
背痛。

35
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,360
Backache.
背痛。

36
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,360
That's right.
没错。

37
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:11,520
So usually when you have a toothache, you experience different symptoms, different things
所以通常当你牙疼时，你会经历不同的症状，不同的事情。

38
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,760
happen to you.
发生在你身上。

39
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:14,120
What's one of these things Marco?
Marco，其中一件事是什么？

40
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:17,280
Well in this case the girl had a swollen cheek.
在这个例子里，那个女孩脸颊肿了。

41
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:19,200
Her cheek is swollen.
她的脸颊肿了。

42
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:21,240
So the cheek is the side of the face.
所以“cheek”是脸的两侧。

43
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:26,240
It's usually where it's a little bit pink and when your cheek is swollen, it looks puffy.
通常是有点粉红的地方，当你的脸颊肿了，它看起来鼓鼓的。

44
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,200
It looks bigger than normal.
看起来比正常大。

45
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,200
That's right.
没错。

46
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:32,560
So for example sometimes you fall and you hurt your finger and it'll get fat and it'll
所以比如有时候你摔倒，伤到手指，它会变胖，会像你说的那样鼓起来。

47
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,920
get puffy as you say.
鼓起来。

48
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:34,920
It's swollen.
它肿了。

49
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:35,920
That's right.
没错。

50
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,320
So anything can be swollen really.
所以实际上任何东西都可能肿。

51
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:42,600
When you hit your toe on something hard and your toe later gets bigger, it's swollen.
当你把脚趾撞到硬物上，后来脚趾变大，那就是肿了。

52
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,640
That's right.
没错。

53
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:48,160
So obviously her cheek is swollen and she has a toothache because apparently her wisdom
所以显然她的脸颊肿了，她牙疼，因为显然她的智齿。

54
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:51,160
teeth or her wisdom tooth is coming out.
她的智齿正在长出来。

55
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,160
All right.
好的。

56
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,200
So wisdom teeth are special teeth.
所以智齿是特殊的牙齿。

57
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:58,280
I don't know if they actually have anything to do with wisdom which means being smart.
我不知道它们是否真的和“wisdom”有关，“wisdom”意思是聪明。

58
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,280
To be wise.
变得明智。

59
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,280
Wise.
明智。

60
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:05,160
But wisdom teeth are those four teeth in the very, very, very back of your mouth.
但智齿是你嘴巴最最最后面的四颗牙齿。

61
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,160
That's right.
没错。

62
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:10,600
So these are the last teeth that come in or the last teeth that grow in your mouth.
所以这些是最后长出来的牙齿，或者最后在你嘴里生长的牙齿。

63
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,760
So I think usually you're 18 or 20 when they come in.
所以我想通常你18或20岁时它们长出来。

64
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,760
That's right.
没错。

65
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,680
A lot of people experience these when they're older.
很多人年纪大些时经历这些。

66
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:20,600
Maybe that's why they call them wisdom teeth because you're older and you're wiser.
也许这就是为什么它们叫智齿，因为你年纪大了，更明智了。

67
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,800
I had them when I was about 14, 13.
我大约14、13岁时就长了。

68
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,960
I was very young.
我很年轻。

69
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:27,040
But these come in the very back.
但这些长在最里面。

70
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,360
They're the furthest away from your lips.
它们离嘴唇最远。

71
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,360
Okay.
好的。

72
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,360
Very good.
很好。

73
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:36,840
So when they come in, sometimes there's not enough space and so they start to press against
所以当它们长出来时，有时空间不够，所以它们开始挤压。

74
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:41,120
the other teeth in your mouth, specifically against your molars.
你嘴里的其他牙齿，特别是你的臼齿。

75
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,600
So molars are other teeth.
所以“molars”是其他牙齿。

76
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,680
These are also in the back of your mouth.
这些也在你嘴巴的后部。

77
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:48,160
You can tell which ones are molars I believe because they're flat on top.
我相信你可以分辨哪些是臼齿，因为它们顶部是平的。

78
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:50,360
They look like a little square.
它们看起来像个小方块。

79
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:53,480
Those are the ones that you use to chew your food with mostly.
这些是你主要用来咀嚼食物的牙齿。

80
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:54,480
Exactly.
没错。

81
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:56,160
They're not pointy like your front teeth.
它们不像你的门牙那样尖。

82
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:58,640
And so molars are in the back of your mouth.
所以臼齿在口腔的后部。

83
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:01,360
Wisdom teeth are in the very back of your mouth.
智齿在口腔的最深处。

84
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:06,080
And molars can be very sore when the wisdom teeth push against them.
当智齿挤压臼齿时，臼齿会非常疼痛。

85
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:09,080
And so in this case, you will have to take your teeth out or the dentist will take your
所以在这种情况下，你必须拔掉牙齿，或者牙医会拔掉你的

86
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,080
teeth out.
牙齿。

87
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:14,200
But what's something we say when we talk about taking the whole tooth out?
但当我们说拔掉整颗牙齿时，我们用什么词呢？

88
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:20,280
Well, in this case, he's going to extract the tooth, but also he's going to extract
嗯，在这种情况下，他要拔掉牙齿，而且还要拔掉

89
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:22,640
the nerve and the root.
神经和牙根。

90
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,640
Okay.
好的。

91
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,640
So nerves are parts of our bodies.
神经是我们身体的一部分。

92
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:29,300
We can't see them, but they help us feel things.
我们看不见它们，但它们帮助我们感知事物。

93
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:34,400
So maybe when someone hits me, the nerves in my arm, they tell my brain that it hurts.
所以，如果有人打我，我手臂里的神经会告诉我的大脑很疼。

94
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:37,960
Well, we also have nerves in our teeth and that's what we're talking about here.
嗯，我们的牙齿里也有神经，这就是我们这里讨论的。

95
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,000
But what's this other thing?
但另一个东西是什么？

96
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,760
You talked about the nerve and the root.
你提到了神经和牙根。

97
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:43,840
It's very similar to a plant, for example.
这很像植物，比如说。

98
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:48,760
You consider that your teeth are like plants and they have little roots that go into your
你可以把牙齿想象成植物，它们有小小的牙根伸进你的

99
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,440
gums.
牙龈。

100
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:54,200
And this is how basically you get teeth stay alive.
这基本上就是牙齿保持活力的方式。

101
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,920
They are fed basically by your body.
它们基本上由你的身体供养。

102
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:56,920
All right.
好的。

103
00:04:56,920 --> 00:05:00,520
So root, like with a tree or a plant, is the very bottom of something.
所以牙根，就像树或植物一样，是某物的最底部。

104
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:04,680
And in this case, to extract means to take out or to take away.
在这种情况下，拔除意味着取出或移除。

105
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:08,920
So the dentist will have to extract the root and the nerve.
所以牙医必须拔除牙根和神经。

106
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,160
So that sounds pretty painful.
听起来很疼。

107
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,800
It's painful, but they have to do it, right?
是疼，但他们必须这么做，对吧？

108
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:18,640
So when the dentist has to extract the tooth, in this case, the nerve and the root and everything,
所以当牙医必须拔牙时，在这种情况下，拔掉神经、牙根和所有东西，

109
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:21,760
in order for you not to feel it, he gives you special drugs.
为了让你不感到疼痛，他会给你一些特殊的药物。

110
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:22,760
What are these drugs called?
这些药物叫什么？

111
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:23,760
These are called anesthetics.
这些叫做麻醉剂。

112
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:24,760
Okay.
好的。

113
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:30,560
So most people, when they are having major surgery, they get anesthetics so that they
所以大多数人，在做大手术时，会使用麻醉剂，这样他们

114
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,760
can't feel anything.
就感觉不到任何东西。

115
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,880
Remember, we were just talking about nerves.
记得我们刚才在讨论神经。

116
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:38,280
Well, anesthetics make it so that you can't feel things through your nerves.
嗯，麻醉剂让你无法通过神经感知事物。

117
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,280
That's right.
没错。

118
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:43,360
So obviously you don't want to feel the pain when somebody's pulling that tooth out of
所以显然你不想在别人把牙齿从你嘴里拔出来时感到疼痛。

119
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,360
your mouth.
你的嘴。

120
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:48,080
So you get an anesthetic and then you don't really feel anything.
所以你用了麻醉剂，然后就感觉不到什么了。

121
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:51,120
You kind of feel something, but you don't really feel pain.
你会有点感觉，但不会真的感到疼痛。

122
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,120
Exactly.
正是。

123
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,800
So anesthetic basically makes you numb.
所以麻醉剂基本上让你麻木。

124
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:55,800
Numb.
麻木。

125
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,800
That's right.
没错。

126
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,800
That's the word, numb.
就是这个词，麻木。

127
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,800
Okay.
好的。

128
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:02,880
So we've taken a look at a lot of vocab, molars, wisdom teeth, etc.
我们看了很多词汇，臼齿、智齿等等。

129
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:16,840
Why don't we listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit with Fluency Builder.
我们为什么不重新听一遍对话，稍后回来进行流利度训练。

130
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,600
What seems to be the problem?
有什么问题吗？

131
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:21,260
I have a really bad toothache.
我牙疼得厉害。

132
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:25,000
My cheek is swollen and I can't eat anything.
我的脸颊肿了，什么都吃不了。

133
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,680
Let's have a look.
让我看看。

134
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:29,840
Hmm, this doesn't look too good.
嗯，情况不太好。

135
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:32,960
I think we may have to pull out your wisdom tooth.
我想我们可能得拔掉你的智齿。

136
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:36,400
It's pressing against your molars and that's one of the reasons you're experiencing so
它正挤压着你的臼齿，这也是你感到这么

137
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,840
much pain.
疼的原因之一。

138
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:44,120
When you pull my tooth, will you also have to extract the nerve and the root?
拔牙的时候，你也要拔掉神经和牙根吗？

139
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,600
First we will take some x-rays and see what we're dealing with.
我们先拍几张X光片，看看情况。

140
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:49,320
I also noticed a small cavity up front here.
我还注意到前面这里有个小蛀牙。

141
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:51,160
So you are going to need a filling.
所以你需要补牙。

142
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:56,080
I guess that's what I get for not flossing or brushing my teeth three times a day.
我想这就是我不每天用牙线或刷三次牙的后果。

143
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,320
It could be that.
可能是这个原因。

144
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,640
Or maybe you are eating too many sweets.
或者你吃太多甜食了。

145
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:03,440
In any case, I'll administer an anesthetic and you won't feel a thing.
不管怎样，我会给你用麻醉剂，你什么都不会感觉到。

146
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:10,180
Alright, so the topic of today's lesson is toothache but it's also basically about learning
好的，今天课程的主题是牙疼，但基本上也是关于学习

147
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:12,640
that you will have to have your tooth taken out.
你将不得不拔牙。

148
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:16,200
So to say this we say, to pull out a tooth.
所以要说这个，我们说，拔牙。

149
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,160
Okay, so that's what the dentist said.
好的，这就是牙医说的。

150
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,720
I think we may have to pull out your wisdom tooth.
我想我们可能得拔掉你的智齿。

151
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,920
Not good news.
不是好消息。

152
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:25,400
Okay, so to pull out means to extract.
好的，所以拔掉意味着取出。

153
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:28,840
So just remember here this is a phrase that has pull out.
所以记住，这是一个包含“拔掉”的短语。

154
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,600
Out would be the preposition here.
“掉”在这里是介词。

155
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:33,240
We wouldn't say pull off or pull at.
我们不会说“拔开”或“拔向”。

156
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,240
We'd say pull out.
我们会说“拔掉”。

157
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:37,600
Like for example, you can pull out a hair or your hair.
比如，你可以拔掉一根头发或你的头发。

158
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,600
Exactly.
正是。

159
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:43,840
Okay, so we're pulling out the wisdom tooth and the dentist first wants to take some x-rays
好的，所以我们拔掉智齿，牙医首先想拍几张X光片

160
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:46,800
to see what we're dealing with.
看看情况。

161
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:53,920
Okay, so to deal with something means to work on it or to have something to do with.
好的，所以“deal with something”意思是处理某事或与某事有关。

162
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:57,240
And so in this case the dentist wants to know, is this serious?
所以在这个例子中，牙医想知道的是：这严重吗？

163
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,960
What are we dealing with here?
我们这里面对的是什么情况？

164
00:07:58,960 --> 00:07:59,960
That's right.
没错。

165
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:02,200
So he's trying to judge the situation.
所以他是在试图判断情况。

166
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:06,840
So maybe what would be another scenario or another situation where you would say, I have
那么，可能还有哪些场景或情况你会说“我得看看我们面对的是什么”？

167
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,480
to see what we're dealing with.
我得看看我们面对的是什么。

168
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:13,920
Well, in the case of the weather and the newsmen who report about the weather, maybe they see
嗯，在天气和播报天气的新闻播报员的情况下，他们可能看到风暴要来了，但必须看雷达和电脑屏幕来了解他们面对的是什么。

169
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:18,240
that a storm is coming but they have to look at the radars and the computer screens to
他们必须看雷达和电脑屏幕来了解他们面对的是什么。

170
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,160
see what they're dealing with.
他们面对的是什么。

171
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:24,240
Is it a serious storm or is it a very weak storm?
是严重的风暴还是微弱的风暴？

172
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,240
They have to evaluate.
他们必须评估。

173
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,240
That's right.
没错。

174
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,240
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

175
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,480
And so we're going to see what we're dealing with.
所以我们要看看我们面对的是什么。

176
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:34,640
And then the girl I think knows that she hasn't really taken good care of her teeth.
然后那个女孩，我觉得她知道她没有好好照顾自己的牙齿。

177
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:39,340
And so she says, I guess that's what I get for not flossing or brushing my teeth.
所以她说：“我猜这就是我不使用牙线或不刷牙的下场。”

178
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:41,880
So that's what you get or that's what I get.
所以“that's what you get”或“that's what I get”。

179
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:49,000
Where the pronoun changes, I, you, he, that's what I get for not taking care of myself.
代词会变化，我、你、他，“这就是我不照顾自己的下场”。

180
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,280
This means it's my fault.
这意思是这是我的错。

181
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,280
I deserved it.
我活该。

182
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,280
I deserve this thing.
我应得的。

183
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:57,000
So I could say, Marco, that's what you get for not doing your homework.
所以我可以这么说，Marco，这就是你不做作业的下场。

184
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
You got a bad grade on your test.
你考试得了低分。

185
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,000
That's right.
没错。

186
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,940
So it's basically a way of saying, that's what you deserve.
所以这基本上是一种说法，意思是“这就是你应得的”。

187
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:05,080
That's the consequence for your actions.
这是你行为的后果。

188
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,080
Exactly.
正是。

189
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,080
Okay.
好的。

190
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,080
And what about our last phrase?
那我们最后一个短语呢？

191
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:11,880
This is something that I hate to hear from doctors and dentists because usually it's
这是我最讨厌从医生和牙医那里听到的话，因为通常都是谎言。

192
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:12,880
a lie.
这是谎言。

193
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:17,720
A dentist will say before he gives you a shot or before he takes your tooth out, you won't
牙医在给你打针或拔牙前会说：“你一点感觉都不会有。”

194
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,200
feel a thing.
你一点感觉都不会有。

195
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,200
That's right.
没错。

196
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:23,660
So he's basically saying you're not going to feel any pain.
所以他基本上是在说你不会感到任何疼痛。

197
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:28,760
But why do we say you won't feel a thing instead of you won't feel anything?
但为什么我们说“you won't feel a thing”而不是“you won't feel anything”？

198
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,760
Just a set phrase.
只是一个固定短语。

199
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:33,720
It's something we say, I would remember it like this because it's more likely to be said
这是我们常说的，我会这样记住它，因为这样说的可能性更大。

200
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,720
in this way.
这样说的可能性更大。

201
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,160
You won't feel a thing.
你一点感觉都不会有。

202
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:40,560
I think it basically means not even one little thing, you're not going to feel that.
我认为它基本上意思是连一点点东西都不会，你不会感觉到。

203
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:46,160
So for example, I'm about to fix someone's back, you know, when you have to pull them
所以比如，我正要帮别人调整背部，你知道，当你需要拉他们让他们的背感觉好点时。

204
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,680
and make their back feel better.
当你需要拉他们让他们的背感觉好点时。

205
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:50,400
I say, you won't feel a thing.
我会说：“你一点感觉都不会有。”

206
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,400
You fix their back.
你调整他们的背。

207
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,400
Okay.
好的。

208
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:55,440
So you won't feel a thing or you won't feel anything.
所以“you won't feel a thing”或“you won't feel anything”。

209
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:59,680
Both are correct, but I think it's more common to hear you won't feel a thing.
两种都对，但我认为更常听到的是“you won't feel a thing”。

210
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:00,680
Okay.
好的。

211
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,720
So why don't we go back?
那我们为什么不回去呢？

212
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:11,440
Let's take one last look at our dialogue and we'll be back in a bit.
让我们最后再看一遍我们的对话，我们一会儿回来。

213
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,200
What seems to be the problem?
有什么问题吗？

214
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,840
I have a really bad toothache.
我牙疼得很厉害。

215
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:19,560
My cheek is swollen and I can't eat anything.
我的脸颊肿了，什么都吃不了。

216
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,240
Let's have a look.
让我看看。

217
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,800
Hmm.
嗯。

218
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,440
This doesn't look too good.
这看起来不太好。

219
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:27,560
I think we may have to pull out your wisdom tooth.
我想我们可能得拔掉你的智齿。

220
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:31,000
It's pressing against your molars and that's one of the reasons you're experiencing so
它正压着你的臼齿，这也是你感到这么疼的原因之一。

221
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,440
much pain.
这也是你感到这么疼的原因之一。

222
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:38,720
When you pull my tooth, will you also have to extract the nerve and the root?
你拔我牙的时候，是不是也要抽掉神经和牙根？

223
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:41,160
First we will take some x-rays and see what we're dealing with.
首先我们会拍些X光片，看看我们面对的是什么情况。

224
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:45,760
I also noticed a small cavity up front here, so you are going to need a filling.
我还注意到前面这里有个小蛀洞，所以你需要补牙。

225
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:50,660
I guess that's what I get for not flossing or brushing my teeth three times a day.
我猜这就是我不每天用牙线或刷牙三次的下场。

226
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:51,920
It could be that.
可能是这个原因。

227
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:54,240
Or maybe you are eating too many sweets.
或者你吃太多甜食了。

228
00:10:54,240 --> 00:11:01,520
In any case, I'll administer an anesthetic and you won't feel a thing.
不管怎样，我会给你打麻药，你一点感觉都不会有。

229
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:05,640
All right so talking about dentists and talking about wisdom teeth, you say that you still
好的，说到牙医和智齿，你说你还有四颗智齿。

230
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:07,080
have all four wisdom teeth.
你还有四颗智齿。

231
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,080
I do.
是的。

232
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,120
They're all still back there.
它们都还在后面。

233
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:13,160
So you didn't need to have them taken out or pulled?
所以你不需要把它们拔掉？

234
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:16,680
No, as my dentist likes to say, I have a big mouth.
不需要，就像我的牙医喜欢说的，我嘴巴大。

235
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:18,000
Which in English has two meanings.
这在英语里有两个意思。

236
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:23,720
A big mouth is not just a large mouth, but also it means you like to talk a lot.
“大嘴巴”不仅指嘴巴大，还指你话多。

237
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:24,720
Right.
对。

238
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:28,520
So, but did you ever have braces for example when you were a kid?
那么，你小时候戴过牙套吗？

239
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:29,520
Oh yes.
哦，戴过。

240
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,520
Oh you had braces.
哦，你戴过牙套。

241
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:34,960
I had a retainer, which is a device that you, it looks like a line across your teeth and
我戴过保持器，那是一种装置，看起来就像一条线横在你的牙齿上，

242
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:39,280
you put it in usually at night, but sometimes during the day and it makes some space in
通常晚上戴，但有时白天也戴，它能在你的嘴里腾出一些空间。

243
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,280
your mouth.
你的嘴里。

244
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,640
But I also had braces after that.
但之后我还戴过牙套。

245
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,640
I hated braces.
我讨厌牙套。

246
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:43,840
I had them for two years.
我戴了两年。

247
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,340
Why did you hate braces?
你为什么讨厌牙套？

248
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:46,340
Because they're uncomfortable.
因为它们不舒服。

249
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:50,480
Well, they don't look very good, especially when you're a 13 year old girl and you want
嗯，它们看起来也不好看，尤其当你是个13岁的女孩，想显得可爱，

250
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:53,840
to look cute and you have this big metal thing in your mouth.
嘴里却塞着这么个大金属玩意儿。

251
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:54,840
That's right.
没错。

252
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,840
Did you have braces?
你戴过牙套吗？

253
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:56,840
No, no, I never had braces.
没有，没有，我从没戴过牙套。

254
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:59,960
Actually it was kind of for a while, I think a lot of people thought it was cool to have
其实有一阵子，我觉得很多人觉得戴牙套很酷。

255
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:00,960
braces.
牙套。

256
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,960
I did not grow up where you grew up.
我成长的地方和你不一样。

257
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,880
It was not cool where I grew up.
在我长大的地方，戴牙套可不酷。

258
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:04,880
I don't know.
我不知道。

259
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:09,560
I think, or it gets to a point where in certain parts, I guess my school was filled with kids
我觉得，或者说在某些地方，大概我的学校全是戴牙套的孩子。

260
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:10,560
that had braces.
都戴着牙套。

261
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,600
So I guess everyone just had really bad teeth.
所以我猜大家牙齿都很糟糕。

262
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:16,440
So obviously the people that didn't have braces kind of were left aside.
所以显然那些没戴牙套的人就被晾在一边了。

263
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,000
So you're like, oh, I want braces.
所以你就会想，哦，我想要牙套。

264
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,560
I want to be part of the group.
我想成为群体的一员。

265
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:23,640
I know sometimes I wish I had glasses, because everyone I know has glasses.
我知道有时候我希望自己戴眼镜，因为我认识的人都有眼镜。

266
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,640
Really?
真的吗？

267
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,640
Yeah.
是啊。

268
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,640
If you have good vision though.
不过如果你视力好的话。

269
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,040
Yeah, it sucks to be perfect, right?
是啊，完美也挺烦的，对吧？

270
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:32,960
Well, this is a really interesting topic and going to the dentist is always complicated.
嗯，这真是个有趣的话题，看牙医总是很复杂。

271
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:37,880
Maybe some of our listeners are dentists themselves or they have some stories that they can share
也许我们的一些听众本身就是牙医，或者他们有些故事可以分享

272
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:38,880
with us.
给我们。

273
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:42,800
Please let us know what you're thinking and share your dentist stories with us on EnglishPod.com.
请告诉我们你的想法，并在EnglishPod.com上分享你的牙医故事。

274
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,120
We'll be waiting for you there.
我们会在那里等你。

275
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,120
All right.
好的。

276
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,120
We'll see you guys then.
那我们到时候见。

277
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,120
Bye.
再见。

278
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,600
Bye.
再见。
